{"word":"G3084 - λυτρόω - lytróō - loo-tro'-o - Redeem","slug":"G3084","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">λυτρόω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>lytróō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>loo-tro'-o"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Redeem"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"- Original: <b><el>λυτρόω</el></b> <p />- Transliteration: <b>Lutroo</b> <p />- Phonetic: <b>loo-tro'-o</b> <p class=\"def\">- Definition: </p> <p class='li260'><b>1.</b> to release on receipt of ransom </p> <p class='li260'><b>2.</b> to redeem, liberate by payment of ransom </p> <p class='li520'><b>a.</b> to liberate </p> <p class='li520'><b>b.</b> to cause to be released to one's self by payment of a ransom </p> <p class='li520'><b>c.</b> to redeem </p> <p class='li520'><b>d.</b> to deliver: from evils of every kind, internal and external </p> <p class=\"origin\"/>- Origin: from <a href=\"#/G3083\">G3083</a> <p />- TDNT entry: 09:49,5 <p />- Part(s) of speech: Verb <p />- Strong's: From <a href=\"#/G3083\">G3083</a>; to <i>ransom</i> (literally or figuratively): - redeem. "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G179\">G179</a>, <a href=\"#/G1955\">G1955</a>, <a href=\"#/G1956\">G1956</a>, <a href=\"#/G2646\">G2646</a>, <a href=\"#/G2647\">G2647</a>, <a href=\"#/G3083\">G3083</a>, <a href=\"#/G3085\">G3085</a>, <a href=\"#/G3086\">G3086</a>, <a href=\"#/G3089\">G3089</a>, <a href=\"#/G359\">G359</a>, <a href=\"#/G360\">G360</a>, <a href=\"#/G487\">G487</a>, <a href=\"#/G629\">G629</a>, <a href=\"#/G630\">G630</a>"}]}